Looking for something fun for your kids to do this summer? Try the Junior Giants Program.

WHAT

Junior Giants at Home - Summer Season 2 (final summer season!)

Free, 4-week season

Live, age-specific practices featuring videos made especially for Junior Giants by Giants Manager Gabe Kapler and his coaching staff

25-35 minute team-style sessions that focus on:

Physical activity & nutrition

Baseball/softball skills & drills

Reading

Bullying Prevention

Junior Giants Four Bases of Character Development:

Leadership, Teamwork Confidence and Integrity

WHEN

Week of July 6 - Week of July 27

Two age-specific live sessions per week led by Junior Giants AmeriCorps Ambassadors.

*Times will be dependent on age and league

WHERE

At home!

WHO

All youth ages 5-18 are welcome!

REGISTER NOW

Head to jrgiantsathome.org/kelseyville/register to register now!

post_text: Just a reminder that starting Monday, July 6 families may pick up meals between 11:00am and 12:30pm at the CLHS Central Kitchen. We will no longer be delivering meals. Each day you will be provided with a lunch for that day and a grab and go breakfast for the next day for all children aged 18 or younger. This program is only for the pick up of meals. You may not eat on site. You must wear a mask when you pick up your meals and please practice social distancing when at the school campus. This free meal program will continue through Friday, July 31. Please contact the Food Services Department at 262 3028 for any questions that you might have.

Lakeport Rotary
April 10 at 4:28 PM ¬∑

The Easter Bunny is coming to Lakeport for a visit! We know this a different Easter this year but we made a few phone calls to see if could get him here for a drive by wave. Well, in true Easter Bunny style, he's completely on board and looking forward to seeing all of your shining faces driving by! Easter Sunday from 12-2pm across from City Hall at Library Park in Lakeport. Please remember this is a DRIVE BY ONLY. There can't be any stopping or congregating in the park. It's just going to be the Bunny and 2 of his Rotarian helpers, properly distanced and masked of course, so please help him share this with everyone by helping him out with this request. Please enter on 1st Street and exit on 3rd so that everyone gets a good chance to blow him a kiss! #EasterBunnyDriveby. #LakeCountyStrong. #KeepTheFaith. #EasterLove

The Clear Lake High School Drama Club invites you to enjoy their production of the hit Broadway musical by Disney, NEWSIES! Based on the real-life Newsboy Strike of 1899, this new Disney musical tells the story of Jack Kelly, a rebellious newsboy who dreams of a life as an artist away from the big city. After publishing giant Joseph Pulitzer raises newspaper prices at the newsboys' expense, Kelly and his fellow Newsies take action!

March 21st @ 7:30pm
March 22nd @ 1pm
March 27th @ 7:30pm
March 28th @ 7:30pm
March 29th @ 1pm

Tickets are $20 for Reserved Seating, $10 for General Seating and $5 for students and children.

Good afternoon Lakeport Elementary friends and families! What a wonderful way to kick off our Attendance Challenge and Spirit Week!! It was fantastic seeing our students and staff comfy in their pajamas today. We had 93.8% of our kiddos here today so we want to give a big THANK YOU to all parents and guardians for getting your students up and to school! Remember that tomorrow, March 3 is "Sports Day" so come dressed in your favorite teams attire. We l also want to encourage you to join us for Family Reading Night on Thursday, March 5th from 5:00pm-7:30pm. This will be an evening full of games, crafts, book giveaways and other secret surprises with a free dinner provided by our PTO starting at 5:00pm. Thank you for always supporting Lakeport Elementary School and have a good evening.

Back-to-back, 14-0 champions are the Clear Lake Cardinals, who wrapped up a second straight perfect North Central League I season with a 61-52 victory Thursday night in Cloverdale. Clear Lake carries a 23-3 record into the North Coast Section Division 5 playoffs next week. The seedings and first-round pairings will be announced Sunday. (Photo courtesy of Trett Bishop)
